Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath LIVE updates: Congress hopes BJP will fulfil poll promises 
18-3-2017 
Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath LIVE updates: Yogi Adityanath elected leader of the BJP Legislature Party in Lucknow on Saturday. (PTI Photo/Nand kumar) Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath LIVE updates: Yogi Adityanath elected leader of the BJP Legislature Party in Lucknow on Saturday. (PTI Photo/Nand kumar)

Yogi Adityanath was named the Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister designate at a meeting of newly-elected MLAs of the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), 312 in total, in Lucknow Saturday. Keshav Maurya and Dinesh Sharma will be his two deputy CMs. Adityanath, Maurya and Sharma will be sworn in tomorrow, at 2.15 pm. They are also expected to address the media on Sunday.

Read | Who is Yogi Adityanath?

Uttar Pradesh LIVE updates:

10.00 pm: Deputy chief minister designate Dinesh Sharma tells ANI he wants to bring good governance in Uttar Pradesh, and that he will work for the poor.

9.40 pm: Former Jammu and Kashmir chief minister Omar Abdullah has just sarcastically tweeted to Mehbooba Mufti, the current CM. He has congratulated her for picking friends and allies who have chosen a CM who once before called for the dead bodies of Muslim women to be raped.

‚ÄúDo you still want to try and fool the people of Kashmir, especially those who trusted you in 2014, that a new Vajpayee like era is starting?‚Äù He asks.

