8.55 pm: The Congress has reacted to Adityanath‚Äôs appointment, wishing the new government well. ‚ÄúWe sincerely hope that BJP Govt in U.P will now rise above rival claims & counter claims for share of power and concentrate upon fulfilling the promises made to people.‚Äù The party lists some of the promises made by the BJP to the people, including loans to farmers, reducing electricity tariff, creating jobs for the youth etc.

Part of the statement put out by its chief spokesperson on Twitter, Randeep S Surjewala‚Äè, says, ‚ÄúExcessive delay in arriving at the decision as also the compulsion to create two posts as deputy chief ministers reflects a bitter conflict to share spoils of power despite overwhelming majority of over 300 MLAs.‚Äù

8.37 pm: Leaders from other parties took to Twitter too Saturday to express their feelings on the new development in Uttar Pradesh. Swaraj Abhiyan party leader Yogendra Yadav, for instance, said people like Yogi Adityanath should not hold any constitutional post.

