4.45 pm: Various TV channels are now announcing Yogi Adityanath as leading the race for UP CM, while Keshav Prasad Maurya and Manoj Sinha may be appointed his deputy CMs.

4.40 pm: In other news, chief secretary Rahul Bhatnagar has issued a circular to government employees to be punctual to work from March 20. The circular asks employees to finish their work on time and warns that action will be taken against those who fail to comply.

‚ÄúThe formation of the new government in Uttar Pradesh is happening soon. The government policies and resolutions have to be fulfilled on time,‚Äù it states.

4.35 pm: Maurya and Om Mathur have arrived at the Lucknow airport, NewsX reports.

4.25 pm: If you‚Äôre just joining us, BJP MLAs are arriving for the party legislature meeting in Lucknow to elect a new leader. Top picks for the post include Manoj Sinha, Rajnath Singh, BJP state president Keshav Prasad Maurya and Gorakhpur MP Yogi Adityanath.

3:55 pm: So Railway Minister Suresh Prabhu is in Mumbai inaugurating a number of projects and flagging off trains. Manoj Sinha, who is MoS Railways, is absent. So does this mean Sinha is going to Lucknow as CM?

3:40 pm: Manoj Sinha is leaving for Lucknow by chartered plane from Varanasi instead of going to Delhi, Times of India is reporting.

3:37 pm: So our readers have spoken. After nearly 2000 votes, our readers think Manoj Sinha is better placed to get the CM job. Rajnath, Maurya and Adityanath all are in contention for second spot. They have 200 votes each.

3:20 pm: There are reports of Yogi Adityanath flying into Delhi sparking further speculation. Additionally, there is no clarity on who would be inducted as ministers.

3:0o pm: BJP workers are assembling in major towns to celebrate the CM candidate announcement.

2:55 pm: RSS is said to be in talks with BJP president Amit Shah on the decision of CM candidate.

2:48 pm: Preparations are in full swing at the Smriti Upvan in Lucknow where the swearing-in function will take place tomorrow.

