12 noon: Welcome to the live blog where we get you up to speed on all the live action happening in New Delhi and Lucknow around the naming of the CM candidate in Uttar Pradesh. Remember, in the recently-concluded elections, the BJP romped home winning 312 seats out of the state‚Äôs 403 seats. The SP-Congress alliance and the BSP tasted defeat.

While the BJP has named its CM candidate in neighbouring Uttarakhand, it has so far not announced its choice in UP. Some of the names doing the rounds are union ministers Rajnath Singh, Manoj Sinha, BJP state president Keshav Prasad Maurya and Gorakhpur MP Yogi Adityanath.

